guidance: Discard. TED translates at form-level. OCDS translates at field-level.
Add an `Organization` object to the `parties` array, set its `.id`, and add 'buyer' to its `.roles`.\n\nSet `buyer.id` to its `.id` and `buyer.name` to its `.name` (see below).

Take the NUTS code in the `CODE` attribute, and map to `.address.region`\n\nThere is an open issue ([#739](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/739)) to add better support for region codes.

Take the country code in the `VALUE` attribute, translate to a country name, and map to `.address.countryName`\n\nThere is an open issue ([#524](https://github.com/open-contracting/standard/issues/524)) to add a `.countryCode` field to the `Address` object, to avoid translation.
[See above](#/F01_2014/CONTRACTING_BODY), but ignore the instructions for `buyer.id` and `buyer.name`.
Discard. If there are multiple parties with the role `buyer`, it is a joint procurement. TED uses the check box as a control element for adding additional contracting authorities.
